    "Loop hunt round 11: step-onto-W IS the goal at path_dist=1 (build 346). After round 10 the worst offender was s=8128 dwarf F5 with 2568 loop turns -- T2156-T4596 = 2441 turns of game_loop period-1 'e' bouncing. Trace: agent on F1's D tile at (16,14) with W east adjacent (path_dist=1, F2-F5 all permanent wedges). stairs_down_mode's wedge step-off cascade preferred the warp direction but my STEP_OFF_SKIP set excluded W tiles (treating them as hazards) -- so the warp_dir candidate 'e' was rejected, fallback walked 'w' (away from W), wayfinder routed back to D, loop. The agent WANTS to step onto W when W is adjacent because that triggers warp_mode where they accept the escape. Fix: in the warp-dir step-off, allow stepping onto W when path_dist==1 (the W tile IS the warp target). General step-off cascade still skips W (don't pick W incidentally when other escapes exist). s=8128 dwarf: F5 4596T starvation (2568 loops) -> F8 1640T starvation (0 loops, 129 kills) -- 3 floors deeper, all loops gone. 45-seed grid: loop_turns_total 12034 -> 9124 (-24%), avg max floor 5.14 -> 5.26, F6 reachers 21 -> 28, sus runs 8 -> 6.",
