    "Loop hunt round 9: warp-direction step-off + tiny-pocket early-term + permawedge D-into-perm gate (build 343). Three patterns from the post-round-8 grid. (1) s=941 dwarf F1 D at (17,14): step-off cascade picked 'n' (toward a T tomb tile) by iteration order even though W was 9 steps south. Agent looped n/s/n/s/T-fight for 1810 turns. Stairs_down_mode step-off now prefers nearest_warp_path.first_step when the warp leads in a clean (non-#/M/W/D/T) direction. Step-off skip set extended to include T so we don't accidentally walk into a tomb mid-loop. s=941 dwarf flipped 2187T F2 starvation -> 3062T F8 killed by UNDEAD DRAGON LICH (276 kills, 0 loops). (2) s=1234 (all 3 races) F1 3-tile pocket: D pointed into a permanent wedge (F2) and no W/U/scrolls -- agent had 0 algorithmic escape and starved at T883 because is_truly_trapped required 1500T-on-floor before firing. New tiny-pocket fast-path: reachable<=20 + reach_pct>=90 + ts_new>=200 + on_floor>=300 + no escape options + kills_on_floor<20 (the kill gate keeps active M-room grinders alive for real combat deaths). s=1234 dwarf 883T starve -> 604T stuck. (3) is_truly_trapped's d_reachable check treated standing-on-D as 'D=None' (BFS skips the player's tile), false-firing the moment the agent stepped onto D. New `on_d_tile = mode == stairs_down_mode` short-circuit. Symmetric on_u_tile. Also: d_reachable now respects the d_into_perm_wedge override so a permawedge-only D doesn't count as escape. 45-seed grid: loop_turns_total 22906 -> 12688 (-45%), sus runs 22 -> 8 (-64%), avg max floor 4.58 -> 4.83, F12 reached for the first time.",
