    "Bug-level: residual Mushroom power on exit + size-aware gear sizing + bug floor is stairs-only (build 341). User: 'The bug weapons and armor are too small to be equipped after the bug level. It's cool if the player shrinks back on the bug level, but the power of the mushroom persists if they leave the level and they get big again and can leave the level.' Then: 'We should remove the bug level from warp destinations and other level skips (zots key, scrolls).' Three coordinated changes. (1) game_systems._restore_size_on_bug_exit called by handle_stairs_up/down + both warp paths whenever the player leaves a bug floor for a non-bug floor AND has consumed the Mushroom once -- the residual power un-shrinks them mid-transition and auto-unequips bug-sized gear so they don't trail a comically-tiny Stinger Blade into normal play. Stair-sealed message now reads 'The Mushroom's power stirs in your veins -- you can leave this floor and grow back to normal size.' (2) Mirror equip filter in the equip handler: while shrunk, bug-only fits ('too tiny'); while normal-sized, BUG gear is rejected ('comically tiny in your hands'). Policy's _best_upgrade + broken-gear swap mirror the same filter so the agent doesn't keep picking a slot the handler will refuse. (3) Bug level removed from random destinations: Scroll of Descent nudges +1/-1 if it'd land on F8; both random warp paths (game_systems.py:3036 + 4248) nudge or stay-put rather than dump the agent into F8 underleveled; Zot's Dimensional Key teleporter (room_actions.py) refuses F8 with 'Zot's magic forbids skipping the bug hive.' 90-run forced-bug grid: F8 entries 9 -> 7 (fewer accidental dumps), F9 reached 7 -> 7 = 100% quest completion among F8 reachers (was 78%), F11 reached 1 -> 3, 7/7 quest-passers equip fully normal gear post-shrunk. s=777 human: F9 starvation w/ Firefly Wand -> F11 combat death w/ Soul Reaver +17 + Full Plate +10.",
